<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79345420-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s1439"><num value="1439">§ 1439.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may issue such regulations as may be necessary to carry out this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79345421-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/92/532/tIII/s308">Pub. L. 92–532, title III, § 308</ref>, formerly § 309, as added <ref href="/us/pl/98/498/tI/s102">Pub. L. 98–498, title I, § 102</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2303">98 Stat. 2303</ref>; renumbered § 308, <ref href="/us/pl/100/627/tII/s203/2">Pub. L. 100–627, title II, § 203(2)</ref>, <date date="1988-11-07">Nov. 7, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/3214">102 Stat. 3214</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/106/513/s9">Pub. L. 106–513, § 9</ref>, <date date="2000-11-13">Nov. 13, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2387">114 Stat. 2387</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id79345422-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id79345423-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id79345424-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior <ref href="/us/pl/92/532/s308">section 308 of Pub. L. 92–532</ref> was classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s1438">section 1438 of this title</ref>, prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/100/627/s203/1">section 203(1) of Pub. L. 100–627</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id79345425-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2000—<ref href="/us/pl/106/513">Pub. L. 106–513</ref> amended section catchline and text generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “If any provision of this Act or the application thereof to any person or circumstances is held invalid, the validity of the remainder of this Act and of the application of such provision to other persons and circumstances shall not be affected thereby.”</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
